The paper focuses on compressed sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). It specifically deals with quantized compressed sensing, which involves quantization of measurements, making it relevant to signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also introduces new algorithms for reconstruction, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Finally, the paper compares the performance of different algorithms, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA).
